## Feature 7: Emergency Support Button 🚨

### Purpose
Provide immediate, one-tap access to crisis resources when users are in severe distress or experiencing suicidal ideation.

### User Benefit
- Instant access to professional help
- No navigation required
- Reduces barriers during crisis

> [!CAUTION]
> **Life-Saving Feature:** This feature must be prominently accessible, reliable, and immediately responsive.

### Functional Requirements

#### FR7.1: Button Placement

**Visibility:**
- **Home Screen:** Prominent red button labeled "Need Help Now?"
- **All Screens:** Floating action button (FAB) in bottom-right corner
- **Chat Feature:** Persistent button during AI conversations

**Design:**
- High contrast (red background, white text)
- Large enough to tap easily (minimum 60x60 pixels)
- Icon: 🚨 or ❤️‍🩹

#### FR7.2: Emergency Resources Screen

**When Button Tapped:**

Immediate display of:

**1. Crisis Helplines (India):**
| Organization | Phone Number | Availability |
|--------------|--------------|--------------|
| **AASRA** | 91-22-27546669 | 24/7 |
| **Vandrevala Foundation** | 1860-2662-345 | 24/7 |
| **iCall** | 91-22-25521111 | Mon-Sat, 8AM-10PM |
| **Snehi** | 91-22-27546669 | 24/7 |
| **COOJ Mental Health Foundation** | +91-833-231-1555 | 24/7 |

**2. One-Tap Call:**
- Tap helpline to call directly
- No need to copy/paste number

**3. Trusted Contact:**
- If configured, option to call/text pre-selected trusted person
- Message template: "I'm not okay. Can you talk?"

**4. Safety Plan:**
- Quick access to user's personalized safety plan
- Coping strategies
- Reasons to live
- Professional contacts

#### FR7.3: Trusted Contact Configuration

**Setup:**
- User can add 1-3 trusted contacts
- Name, phone number, relationship
- Optional: Pre-written message templates

**Privacy:**
- User controls when to contact
- No automatic notifications (user autonomy)

#### FR7.4: Safety Plan Creation

**Guided Safety Plan:**

1. **Warning Signs:** "What tells you that you're in crisis?"
   - Example: "I start thinking everyone would be better off without me"

2. **Coping Strategies:** "What helps you feel better?"
   - Example: "Listening to music, talking to my friend, going for a walk"

3. **Reasons to Live:** "What are your reasons to keep going?"
   - Example: "My family, my dog, my dreams"

4. **Professional Contacts:** "Who can you call for professional help?"
   - Therapist name and number
   - Crisis helplines

5. **Safe Environment:** "How can you make your environment safer?"
   - Example: "Remove harmful objects, stay with someone"

**Storage:**
- Saved locally and encrypted
- Accessible offline
- Can be updated anytime

### User Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[User Taps Emergency Button] --> B[Emergency Resources Screen]
    B --> C{User Choice}
    C -->|Call Helpline| D[Direct Call to Selected Helpline]
    C -->|Contact Trusted Person| E[Call/Text Trusted Contact]
    C -->|View Safety Plan| F[Display Safety Plan]
    C -->|Create Safety Plan| G[Guided Safety Plan Creation]
    D --> H[Log Crisis Event]
    E --> H
    F --> H
    G --> I[Save Safety Plan]
    I --> H
    H --> J[Follow-Up Check-In Next Day]
```

### Follow-Up Protocol

**Next Day Check-In:**
- Push notification: "How are you feeling today?"
- Mood check-in
- Suggest professional help if still in crisis
- Offer to connect with therapist

### Privacy Considerations
- Crisis events logged for user's own tracking
- Never shared without consent
- User can delete crisis logs

### Safety Mechanisms
- Button always accessible (cannot be disabled)
- Works offline (cached helpline numbers)
- No judgment or barriers to access

---

## Feature 8: Personalized Self-Care Plan

### Purpose
Generate customized self-care recommendations based on user's mood trends, workload stress, and family pressure patterns.

### User Benefit
- Tailored advice (not generic)
- Actionable steps
- Adapts to changing needs

### Functional Requirements

#### FR8.1: Data Inputs for Personalization

**Sources:**
1. Daily mood check-in trends
2. Workload stress levels
3. Family pressure assessments
4. Feature usage patterns (which tools used most)
5. Crisis events (if any)

#### FR8.2: Self-Care Recommendation Engine

**Algorithm Logic:**

**If High Workload Stress:**
- Suggest: "Take a mental health day"
- Suggest: "Set work boundaries (no emails after 7 PM)"
- Suggest: "Talk to manager about workload"
- Suggest: "Use breathing exercises during work breaks"

**If High Family Pressure:**
- Suggest: "Practice boundary-setting with family"
- Suggest: "Journal about your authentic desires"
- Suggest: "Connect with peer support on family expectations"
- Suggest: "Limit family gatherings if needed"

**If Both High:**
- Suggest: "Consider professional counseling"
- Suggest: "Prioritize one area at a time"
- Suggest: "Build a support network outside work and family"

**If Improving Trends:**
- Celebrate: "Your stress has decreased 20% this month!"
- Encourage: "Keep using the tools that are working"

#### FR8.3: Self-Care Plan Components

**Weekly Plan Includes:**

1. **Priority Action:** Most important step this week
   - Example: "Schedule a therapy session"

2. **Daily Micro-Actions:** Small, achievable tasks
   - Example: "Take 5-minute breathing break at lunch"

3. **Social Connection:** Reduce isolation
   - Example: "Reach out to one friend this week"

4. **Physical Self-Care:** Body-mind connection
   - Example: "Go for a 20-minute walk 3 times this week"

5. **Emotional Processing:** Safe expression
   - Example: "Journal for 10 minutes before bed"

#### FR8.4: Progress Tracking

**Track Completion:**
- User checks off completed actions
- Visual progress bar
- Weekly summary of completion rate

**Adaptive Adjustments:**
- If user consistently skips certain actions, suggest alternatives
- If user completes all actions, increase challenge slightly

### User Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[App Analyzes User Data] --> B[Generate Personalized Plan]
    B --> C[Display Weekly Self-Care Plan]
    C --> D[User Reviews Recommendations]
    D --> E{Accept Plan?}
    E -->|Yes| F[Set Reminders]
    E -->|Modify| G[Customize Actions]
    G --> F
    F --> H[Daily Reminders for Actions]
    H --> I[User Completes Actions]
    I --> J[Check Off Completed]
    J --> K[Weekly Review]
    K --> L[Generate Next Week's Plan]
```

### Example Self-Care Plans

**For Priya (High Workload Stress):**
> **This Week's Self-Care Plan**
> 
> **Priority Action:** Talk to your manager about workload distribution
> 
> **Daily Actions:**
> - ✅ Use box breathing during lunch break
> - ✅ Stop working by 8 PM (3 days this week)
> - ✅ Take a 10-minute walk after work
> 
> **Social Connection:** Call a friend who makes you laugh
> 
> **Emotional Processing:** Journal about one thing you're proud of each day

**For Arjun (High Family Pressure):**
> **This Week's Self-Care Plan**
> 
> **Priority Action:** Write down YOUR career goals (not family's expectations)
> 
> **Daily Actions:**
> - ✅ Practice saying "I need to think about that" when family pressures you
> - ✅ Spend 15 minutes on a hobby you enjoy
> - ✅ Read peer stories about family pressure
> 
> **Social Connection:** Connect with peer support community
> 
> **Emotional Processing:** Journal about what YOU want from life

### Privacy Considerations
- Self-care plans stored locally
- User can share progress (optional)
- No external access

---

## Feature 9: Progress & Hope Tracker 🌱

### Purpose
Visualize emotional improvement over time, celebrate small wins, and build hope through tangible evidence of progress.

### User Benefit
- See that things are getting better (even slowly)
- Motivation to continue using coping tools
- Combat hopelessness with data-driven hope

### Functional Requirements

#### FR9.1: Metrics Tracked

**Emotional Metrics:**
1. **Average Mood:** Weekly/monthly average mood score
2. **Stress Levels:** Trend of stress over time
3. **Good Days:** Count of days with positive mood
4. **Crisis-Free Days:** Days without severe distress

**Behavioral Metrics:**
1. **Tool Usage:** Frequency of breathing exercises, journaling, etc.
2. **Self-Care Completion:** % of self-care plan completed
3. **Community Engagement:** Participation in peer support

**Workload Metrics:**
1. **Average Weekly Hours:** Trend over time
2. **Overtime Reduction:** Decrease in overtime hours
3. **Weekend Work:** Frequency of weekend work

**Family Pressure Metrics:**
1. **Family Stress Score:** Trend over time
2. **Guilt Levels:** Reduction in guilt feelings

#### FR9.2: Visualizations

**1. Mood Trend Line Graph:**
- X-axis: Time (weeks/months)
- Y-axis: Average mood score
- Color-coded: Green (improving), Yellow (stable), Red (declining)

**2. Stress Reduction Chart:**
- Before/after comparison
- Percentage improvement

**3. Small Wins Calendar:**
- Calendar view with positive days highlighted
- Visual representation of progress

**4. Tool Effectiveness:**
- Which tools correlate with mood improvement
- Personalized recommendations based on data

#### FR9.3: Milestone Celebrations

**Automated Celebrations:**

**7 Days of Check-Ins:**
> 🎉 **Milestone Unlocked!**
> 
> You've completed 7 days of mood check-ins. Building self-awareness is the first step to feeling better. Keep going!

**First Month:**
> 🌟 **One Month Strong!**
> 
> You've been using the app for a month. Your average stress has decreased by 15%. You're making progress!

**Stress Reduction:**
> 💪 **Progress Alert!**
> 
> Your stress levels have decreased by 25% over the past month. The tools you're using are working. Keep it up!

**Crisis-Free Month:**
> 🌈 **Hope Milestone!**
> 
> You've gone a full month without a crisis event. That's incredible progress. You're building resilience.

#### FR9.4: Hope-Building Messages

**Weekly Summary:**
> **This Week's Wins:**
> - You completed 5 mood check-ins
> - Your average mood improved from 😐 to 🙂
> - You used breathing exercises 3 times
> - You connected with peer support
> 
> **Small progress is still progress. You're doing great.**

### User Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Open Progress Tracker] --> B[View Dashboard]
    B --> C[Mood Trend Graph]
    B --> D[Stress Reduction Chart]
    B --> E[Small Wins Calendar]
    B --> F[Milestone Achievements]
    C --> G[Detailed Insights]
    D --> G
    E --> G
    F --> H[Share Progress (Optional)]
    G --> I[Personalized Encouragement]
```

### Insights Provided

**Example Insights:**
- "Your mood improves on days you use breathing exercises"
- "Your stress is lower when you work fewer than 50 hours/week"
- "Family pressure affects your mood more on weekends"
- "You've had 12 good days this month—that's 40% of the month!"

### Privacy Considerations
- All data stored locally
- User can export data for personal use
- Optional: Share anonymized progress in peer support for encouragement

### Safety Mechanisms
- If progress stagnates or declines, suggest professional help
- Avoid toxic positivity ("Just think positive!")
- Acknowledge setbacks as normal

---

## Summary: Feature Integration

All 9 features work together to create a comprehensive support system:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Daily Mood Check-In] --> B[Early Detection]
    C[Workload Tracker] --> B
    D[Family Pressure Assessment] --> B
    B --> E{Distress Level?}
    E -->|Low| F[Encouragement]
    E -->|Medium| G[Suggest Tools]
    E -->|High| H[Crisis Intervention]
    G --> I[AI Chat]
    G --> J[Mental Health Tools]
    G --> K[Peer Support]
    H --> L[Emergency Button]
    L --> M[Professional Help]
    F --> N[Progress Tracker]
    G --> N
    I --> N
    J --> N
    K --> N
    N --> O[Personalized Self-Care Plan]
    O --> A
```

**The Cycle:**
1. **Detect** distress early (Features 1-3)
2. **Support** immediately (Features 4-6)
3. **Intervene** in crisis (Feature 7)
4. **Guide** with personalized care (Feature 8)
5. **Motivate** with progress (Feature 9)
6. **Repeat** for continuous support

